://api.github.com/users/mcollina/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mcollina/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mcollina/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mcollina/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mcollina/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mcollina/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2020-01-31T10:04:43Z","updated_at":"2020-01-31T10:04:43Z","body":"I've seen this happening so many times that is pretty clear that newbie JS developers do not understand the critical differences between `async function` and `function`. This issue originates from that request. I'm not going to do a survey because the sample for that survey are going to be totally skewed.\r\n\r\nI'm happy to make Fastify return a 500 and an error in that case. Practically, we should change these three lines: https://github.com/fastify/fastify/blob/7fa4bddca07aac18e0600cff40d97b95a96ab970/lib/handleRequest.js#L112-L114.\r\nMaking it return would change that block to:\r\n\r\n```js\r\n  var result = reply.context.handler(request, reply)\r\n  if (result) {\r\n    if (typeof result.then === 'function') {\r\n      wrapThenable(result, reply)\r\n    } else {\r\n      reply.send(new Error('return a promise or use an async function in the route handler'))\r\n      // or reply.send(result)\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n```\r\n\r\nI think this change should be part of v3.\r\n ","author_association":"MEMBER","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/fastify/fastify/issues/comments/580668895/reactions","total_count":4,"+1":4,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"mcollina","id":52195,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjUyMTk1","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/52195?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/mcoll